From Daniel Coleman Subject Re pc junior usable In article Welch Bryan writes My fiance has a pc junior and wants to upgrade to a full Does anyone know if we could use the monitor it came with on a new machine I heard it's MCGA or EGA but not sure Also does it use cards so we can use the drive controller floppy etc The only things you'll be able to salvage from the junior are the floppy drives and The floppies are and the monitor is CGA but you will need an adaptor cable to use The junior does not use standard Unless you're really strapped for cash you should just junk the thing and buy new Dan Daniel Matthew Coleman Internet The University of Texas at Austin DECnet UTXVMS DCOLEMAN Electrical Computer Engineering BITNET DCOLEMAN UTXVMS